  "target_concept_id": "base_rate_neglect",
  "modality": "socratic",
  "steps": [
    {
      "step_number": 1,
      "concept_id": "base_rate",
      "modality": "reading",
      "objective": "Quickly re-activate the definition of a base rate as the population-level frequency that exists before any test evidence is considered.",
      "pedagogy_principle": "spaced_repetition"
    },
    {
      "step_number": 2,
      "concept_id": "conditional_probability",
      "modality": "interactive",
      "objective": "Work through a P(disease | positive test) calculation, explicitly separating the test's hit rate from the prior, to prime the machinery the learner needs for medical-test problems.",
      "pedagogy_principle": "worked_example"
    },
    {
      "step_number": 3,
      "concept_id": "base_rate_neglect",
      "modality": "socratic",
      "objective": "Through guided questioning on the failed medical-test problem, surface the learner's intuition that the test result alone determines the answer, then force them to confront how the low base rate changes the conclusion.",
      "pedagogy_principle": "elaboration"
    },
    {
      "step_number": 4,
      "concept_id": "representativeness_heuristic",
      "modality": "socratic",
      "objective": "Contrast a representativeness-driven judgment with a base-rate-neglect case so the learner can distinguish why each ignores base rates, sharpening the target concept by comparison.",
      "pedagogy_principle": "interleaving"
    },
    {
      "step_number": 5,
      "concept_id": "base_rate_neglect",
      "modality": "interactive",
      "objective": "Have the learner independently solve a fresh medical-test probability problem, justifying each step and explicitly weighting the base rate, to verify the misconception is corrected.",
      "pedagogy_principle": "desirable_difficulty"
    }
  ],
  "rationale": "The learner has failed base_rate_neglect twice via reading, despite mastering both prerequisites — repeating an expository read is unlikely to help. The failures stem from a robust intuition (ignoring the prior in favor of the vivid test result), which is a misconception best surfaced through dialogue. Hence the KEY teaching step (3) is socratic, matching the concept's modality hints. We scaffold with a spaced-repetition refresh of base_rate, a worked conditional-probability calculation to supply the procedural tool, then interleave with the easily-confused representativeness heuristic, and finally check transfer with an independent retrieval problem at difficulty 3."
}

